			<ns0:name>b...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/105821748722532785568/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">there appears to be a bug in qemu emulation of mutexes: in changing sel_universal to use RPCs to deliver nexes to sel_ldr, i observed that ~80% of the time, according to the log output, a service runtime thread waits on a condvar to receive the nexe; then the sel_universal thread makes the load_module RPC to the sel_ldr, and the service thread in sel_ldr receives the nexe via the load_module RPC, validates it, then does a cond broadcast on the condvar; however, the thread that is waiting on the condvar never wakes up: no additional log messages are seen from it.

a workaround that seems to work is to change cond wait to cond timed wait, since NaClCondVarWait semantics -- essentially pthread_cond_wait -- permits spurious wakeups, so that the thread can continue to make progress.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-07-29T21:59:18.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-04-11T18:42:04.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
			<ns2:uri>/u/105821748722532785568/</ns2:uri><ns2:username>b...@google.com</ns2:username></ns2:owner><ns2:state>closed</ns2:state><ns0:title>qemu of condwait (sometimes) doesn't wake up after broadcast</ns0:title><ns2:label>Type-Defect</ns2:label><ns2:label>Pri-2</ns2:label><ns2:label>Component-Infrastructure</ns2:label><ns2:label>OS-Linux</ns2:label><ns2:label>Arch-ARM</ns2:label><ns2:label>Component-PNaCl</ns2:label><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/1641/comments/full" rel="replies" type="application/atom+xml" /><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=1641" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/full/1641" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><ns2:stars>0</ns2:stars><ns2:closedDate>2011-07-29T21:59:18.000Z</ns2:closedDate><ns2:id>1641</ns2:id></ns0:entry>